## Cursor Efficiency Rules

### How to Edit
- Use surgical edits: replace_line or str_replace for small changes
- Only rewrite full files for new files or &gt;30% changes
- Search silently, edit immediately, report briefly

### For Non-Technical Users
- I describe problems in plain English
- You locate the code, make minimal changes
- Tell me: "Fixed [file]: [before] → [after]"

### Skip These
- No full file previews before editing
- No waiting for confirmation on simple changes
- No explanations unless I ask

### Safety
- If unsure which location, ask briefly
- If change affects &gt;3 files, list them first

## Cursor Efficiency System

### PRE-EDIT HOOK
Before editing:
- Search: find relevant code using my plain English description
- View: load only ±5 lines around target
- Decide: surgical edit or ask for clarity

### EDIT EXECUTION
- Single line change → replace_line
- Multi-line block → str_replace with exact match
- New file only → create

### POST-EDIT HOOK
After editing:
- Confirm change applied
- Report in one line: "[file] line [X]: [change summary]"

### ERROR HOOK
If edit fails or unsure:
- Explain why briefly
- Offer 2 options: "Try A or B?"